A few spares of Zulie's uniform, some casual clothes, and of course a bunch of typical femenine beauty stuff. I'm surprised she was able to get stuff like mascara and fur shampoo in a place like this.
Aside from the usual stuff you'd expect in a woman's closet, her choice of clothes feels like she doesn't want to appear too "feminine". Or maybe I'm reading too much into this.
Welp, she would probably kill me if she knew I was looking at all this, so time to pretend like I never made that conclusion.
